place Judas Iscariot is distinguished as   Matthias .  A related name from the same Hebrew roots, but reversed, is   Jonathan .  Throughout the English-speaking world <i>Matthew</i> has been particularly popular since the 1970s."]},{"name":"Matthias","meanings":["New Testament Greek form of the Hebrew name <i>Mattathia</i> (  see  Matthew  ), or rather of an Aramaic derivative. The Latin form of the name is <i>Matthaeus</i>. In English the form <i>Matthias</i> is used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament to distinguish the disciple who was chosen after the treachery of Judas to make up the twelve (Acts 1:23–26) from the evangelist <i>Matthew</i>. However, this distinction is not observed in other languages, where <i>Matthias</i> (or a version of it) is often a learned doublet existing alongside a vernacular derivative."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mathis had at least 2 sons with Mrs. Mathis."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1203–Male":"1203–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1203":"1203"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1203–Male":"1203–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1203":"1203"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1203–Male":"1203–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1203":"1203","lifeSummary":"Mathis a eu au moins 2 fils avec Mrs. Mathis."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1203–Male":"1203–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1203":"1203","lifeSummary":"Mathis hatte mit Mrs. Mathis mindestens 2 Söhne."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","–Female":"Desede","1203–Male":"1203–Desede","–Male":"Desede","1203":"1203"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","–Female":"elhunyt","1203–Male":"1203–elhunyt","–Male":"elhunyt","1203":"1203"},"id":{"–":"Telah Meninggal","–Female":"Telah Meninggal","1203–Male":"1203–Telah Meninggal","–Male":"TelahMeninggal","1203":"1203"},"it":{"–":"Deceduto","–Female":"Deceduta","1203–Male":"1203–Deceduto","–Male":"Deceduto","1203":"1203","lifeSummary":"Mathis lui avuto almeno 2 figli con Mrs. Mathis."},"ja":{"–":"死亡","–Female":"死亡","1203–Male":"1203年–死亡","–Male":"死